added.title: The Curse
added.description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

added.title: The Ghouls
added.description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The Origins
added.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

added.title: The Origins Part 2
added.description: Via the sewers, Darwin finds himself flushed out to sea. He is terrified but determined to make his way back to the Wattersons. However, a fish can't get very far on land so Darwin will have to do millions of years of evolution in a matter of hours if he's going to get home safe and sound.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Under the Overpass
added.description: Craig and his friends travel to find honeysuckle in the creek but discover a whole new part of the creek.

added.title: The Invitation
added.description: Craig and his friends are invited to an exclusive tea party with delicious desserts, if they can last to the end of the party.

added.title: Vulture's Nest
added.description: Craig and his friends start a band, but Craig is haunted by a frightening nightmare.

added.title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
added.description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

added.title: Dude Where's Macaw
added.description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

added.title: Way Back Wendel
added.description: Courtney must deliberately lose a challenge or let the entire world go back in time. It's a really hard choice for her.

added.title: Stingin' in the Rain
added.description: When Chef gets locked outside in a storm, the kids mistakenly assume he's a robber and decide to protect the Daycare, by any means necessary.

added.title: Dissing Cousins Part 1
added.description: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

added.title: Dissing Cousins Part 2
added.description: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

added.title: For a Few Duncans More
added.description: While trying to photocopy his butt on Chef's fancy new copier Duncan accidentally makes an entire other Duncan. Great! This other Duncan can do all the school stuff while the real Duncan chills. But things go badly when the other Duncan decides to copy himself so he can chill too.

added.title: He Who Wears the Clown
added.description: After trying on the nose of a clown Owen learns that this is how clowns are made and he is stuck as a clown until he can trick someone else into asking to try on the nose.

added.title: Us 'R' Toys
added.description: When Chef brings in some old toys from his childhood he, Duncan and Gwen, each get magically sucked into one of the toys and need to find a way to get back into their own bodies.

added.title: Stakes Part 5: May I Come In?
added.description: Finn, Jake, Marceline, and PB set out to hunt down the Vamps. But who is hunting them?

added.title: Stakes Part 6: Take Her Back
added.description: While Princess Bubblegum searches for a cure for Marceline, Finn & Jake take on one of the Vamps themselves.

added.title: Death in Bloom
added.description: Finn and Jake are terrible house sitters and have to go on a quest to replace Princess Bubblegum's rare flower.

added.title: Slumber Party Panic
added.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

added.title: Henchman
added.description: While trying to rescue a helpless stranger, Finn becomes Marceline's slave.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: A New Dawn
added.description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: Apple and Onion must find a way to use Burger's trampoline without making him feel used.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple needs to acquire a lifetime supply of toilet paper to finish his modern art sculpture.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple has to find a way not to lose his best friend.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Apple tries to survive a weekend alone while taking care of Onion's plant.

added.title: The Never-Realm
added.description: The ninja arrive in the Never-Realm where they quickly find themselves overwhelmed. Luckily, they are taken in by a tribe of Ice Fishers who tell them Zane has been imprisoned by the evil Ice Emperor.

added.title: Fire Maker
added.description: The Ice Emperor learns of the ninja's arrival and sends his Blizzard Samurai warriors to destroy them and the villagers who sheltered them.

added.title: An Unlikely Ally
added.description: Lloyd runs afoul of the Ice Emperor's Blizzard Samurai but is rescued by a strange wolf with whom an unlikely friendship develops.

added.title: The Absolute Worst!
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, three criminals learn of the ninja's absence and stage a breakout of Kryptarium Prison, telling tall tales of how they were captured as they go.

added.title: The Message
added.description: Lloyd and his wolf-companion find a cave with the mech inside and a message from Zane that provides a clue to his fate.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: In Your Own Skin
added.description: When Valentino is mocked for his lack of style, he's determined to get a designer hoodie to prove he has a sense of fashion, which turns out to be harder than it looks.
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Ghosted
added.description: Vic makes a ghost friend but when she interferes with his shot at being part of the cool kids' Tlatchtli team, he must choose between the two.
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Carmelita
added.description: Chata loans Xochi a car under the condition that Vic and Val can get rides when they need. However, the car becomes aggressive towards V&V and attacks!
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Mandora - The Evil Chaser
added.description: Lion-O "accidentally" releases a whole space prison-full of space criminals and winds up on the wrong side of the law. On the right side of the law is Mandora the Evil Chaser, a no nonsense space cop! Lion-O's gonna have to work real hard to prove he's not a criminal, just a little bit of an oaf!

added.title: Dr. Dometome
added.description: Lion-O is tasked with mapping the beaches of Third Earth, which leads to him somehow draining the oceans of all water entirely. Woops! But a mysterious scientist with a robotic frog says they can fix everything by traveling under the earth, which is just the kinda crazy adventure Lion-O is all about!

added.title: The Trial
added.description: Steven goes on trial.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Not Impressed
added.description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.

added.title: Enemy Mime
added.description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.

added.title: Outfoxed
added.description: When Rufus and Reg come to swindle the town, Sheriff Mao Mao teaches them a lesson in justice.

added.title: Bao Bao's Revenge
added.description: When Mao Mao's old partner threatens the kingdom, his friends will need to learn about his past in order to protect the present.

added.title: Popularity Conquest
added.description: When Mao Mao discovers that he is not as popular as Badgerclops and Adorabat, they decide to reinvent him as a kinder, cuddlier hero.

added.title: Los Vegetales
added.description: Gumball y Darwin solo quieren holgazanear todo el día, pero terminan teniendo que salvar al resto de la familia.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Los Espectros
added.description: Halloween ya no es lo que solía ser. ¿Pueden Gumball y Darwin ayudar a los monstruos a recuperar su capacidad de asustar?
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La prueba
added.description: Steven va a juicio.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: Con tantos cambios en su vida, Steven intenta encontrar su lugar en el mundo.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: The Trade
added.description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal.

added.title: Dog King Clarence
added.description: When Clarence's neighbor Gale recruits him to dog sit for her, he knows it will be a breeze, being the self-proclaimed "Dog King," Clarence knows all there is to know about pups. Nevertheless, Gale's dog proves to be a little more challenging than he expects!

added.title: The Phone Call
added.description: A threatening phone call from a stranger causes the gang to panic.

added.title: Small World: Maze Daze Part 3
added.description: The girls must enter a cursed jungle temple to obtain the last Heart Stone.

added.title: Small World: Heart to Heartstone Part 4
added.description: In the stunning conclusion, the girls learn Lester has one more trick up his sleeve.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 1
added.description: When a mysterious shark-bot named Hammerbyte kidnaps comatose Windblade, Bee and Chromia must chase him into the depths of the Argon Sea to retrieve her.

added.title: Dweller in the Depths Part 2
added.description: Optimus receives a dire warning from the Primes as Chromia and Bee pursue Windblade into a waking Titan under the sea.

added.title: Silent Strike Part 1
added.description: Optimus and the Autobots infiltrate Decepticon Territory to destroy the Dark Matrix Megatron stole from a mysterious bot known only as "The Other One."

added.title: Silent Strike Part 2
added.description: Megatron tries desperately to prevent The Other One from entering their universe.

added.title: The Other One Part 1
added.description: The Other One and his Super Soldiers arrive, forcing Optimus and Megatron to fight together.

added.title: The Other One Part 2
added.description: The Other One reveals himself as an all-powerful Megatron from a universe where Optimus Prime is no more.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: Pequena Escuela Madre
added.description: Bienvenidos a la Pequeña Escuela Madre, un lugar en la Tierra donde Gemas de todo el universo pueden aprender a vivir juntas pacíficamente. Pero hay una Gema que se rehúsa a asistir.

added.title: Consejos
added.description: Amatista ha estado ayudando a las Gemas de Pequeña Escuela Madre a encontrar trabajo, pero Steven no está seguro de su enfoque.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Azulejo
added.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

added.title: Cambio De Edad
added.description: Durante una parada en la megatienda Shoppë, Nanny Nightmare -una niñera que se volvió loca- transforma a Ben y Gwen en bebés. Y nada la detendrá en su intento de reorganizar el mundo a imagen y semejanza de su guardería.

added.title: Tienes Mas Ahi Atras?
added.description: Rad se pone a prueba cuando un cliente necesita algo de la misteriosa habitación trasera.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La Breve Carrera De La Nina Suertuda
added.description: Cuando un hechicero jugador de cosplay pone las manos sobre una varita mágica real en la convención Comic Con, Ben consigue la ayuda de Gwen para impedir que Hex la recupere: Gwen engaña al hechicero malvado y le hace creer que es una poderosa maga...ila única e inimitable Niña Suertuda!

added.title: Do You Have Any More in the Back?
added.description: Rad is put to the test when a customer needs something from the mysterious back room.

added.title: Presentando a Joe Kaffi
added.description: K.O. intenta ayudar a Joe Kaffi, su comediante favorito.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Presenting Joe Cuppa
added.description: KO tries to help his favorite comedian, Joe Cuppa.

added.title: Leyendas del Senor Gar
added.description: Rad y Enid recuerdan la época en la que comenzaron a trabajar en el almacén y entendieron lo fabuloso que es el Sr. Gar.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: El Reino del Jamas
added.description: Los ninja llegan al Never-Realm donde rápidamente se sienten abrumados. Afortunadamente, son recibidos por una tribu de pescadores de hielo que les dicen que Zane ha sido encarcelado por el malvado Emperador de hielo.

added.title: Bajo el Puente
added.description: Craig y sus amigos viajan para encontrar madreselva en el arroyo, pero descubren una parte completamente nueva del arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Legends of Mr. Gar
added.description: Rad and Enid reminisce about when they started working at the bodega and learned how amazing Mr. Gar really is.

added.title: La Invitacion
added.description: Craig y sus amigos están invitados a una exclusiva merienda con deliciosos postres, si es que pueden quedarse hasta el final de la fiesta.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Subterranean Homesick Blues/Honey Struck
added.description: Subterranean Homesick Blues: The AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years more advanced./Honey Struck: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan who is nothing but sticky trouble.

added.title: Nido de buitres
added.description: Craig y sus amigos forman una banda, pero a Craig lo atormenta una pesadilla aterradora.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Shun Shine/Ronin Son
added.description: Shun Shine: The AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell./Ronin Son: When Shun's cousin Masato Kazami claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend by their side.

added.title: Framing Device/Bad Actors
added.description: Framing Device: When confronted by China Riot Lia learns to evolve Pegatrix after realizing the true meaning behind her filming obsession./Bad Actors: Dan tries to lie about evolving Drago and gets exposed while the team face off against Duran Dane and his unhappy Bakugan Nillious.

added.title: Tripped Up/Power Tripp
added.description: Tripped Up: Dan and Wynton stumble on both a possible hidden location of the Mind Core Cell and Colonel Tripp who wants the energy source for himself./Power Tripp: After a falling out with Dan, Wynton is mind-controlled by Tripp who stages an attack to ignite a war between Brawlers and the Military.

added.title: A Real Steal/Lightning Unleashed
added.description: A Real Steal: Dan embarks on a solo adventure to outdo Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers and winds up having to be saved by them instead./Lightning Unleashed: Lightning uncovers the Mind Core Cell buried beneath the Earth and battles Stata the Hunter in an effort to protect its secret.

added.title: Rules of Engagement
added.description: Princess Looma returns to claim Ben as her husband, and she's not going to let anyone stand in her way!  (Featuring Julie and Ship.)

added.title: Big Bad Dreams
added.description: When Namagem starts using his Hypno powers to haunt Aki's dreams, our hero must face his fears in the dreamscape.

added.title: License to Drill
added.description: Mega Man teams up with Bert Wily to take down Drill Man, whose plan to construct hundreds of drill shaped high rises has put Silicon City in both aesthetic and physical danger!

added.title: Hogar, Dulce Hogar
added.description: Los Fantásticos vuelven a casa y se dan cuenta de que el tiempo no ha pasado. Pronto descubren que su conocimiento acerca de las batallas ha aumentado de forma exponencial.

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: Un Golpe de Ternura
added.description: Después de derrotar a Strata, Los Fantásticos se dan cuenta de que no volvieron solos, sino con un Bakugan parecido a un panda que les dará muchos problemas.

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
added.description: While hiking on a dormant volcano, Aki sets out to retrieve Ashley's lost camera and, as Mega Man, to stop Fire Man from setting off an eruption!

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: El Hijo Prodigo
added.description: Mientras los Fantásticos intentan evolucionar a sus Bakugan como lo hizo Dan con Drago, el primo de Shun, Masato, llega a la ciudad para llevarlo de regreso a Japón.

added.title: A Split End
added.description: After replicating Cut Man's powers, Mega Man goes on a perfectionist spree, putting him on a collision course with Cut Man himself, whose latest stint as a hairdresser hasn't helped him overcome his own compulsions.

added.title: El Poder Interior
added.description: Masato Kazami vuelve junto con los guardaespaldas de la familia para llevar a Shun a Japón, pero esta vez, Shun y Hydorous tienen una sorpresa preparada.

added.title: OTTO Motive
added.description: Kevin and Rook run into an old enemy from the Null Void while attending an intergalactic auto show. (Re-introducing classic Ben alien, Upgrade.)

added.title: El Baul de los Recuerdos
added.description: Al ser confrontada por China Riot, Lia logra evolucionar a Pegatrix cuando comprende la verdadera razón de su obsesión por las cámaras.

added.title: Malos Actores
added.description: Alguien expone a Dan por mentir acerca de la evolución de Drago, mientras el equipo se enfrenta a Duran Dane y su desdichado Bakugan, Nillious.

added.title: El Atrapador
added.description: Dan y Wynton se encuentran con la posible ubicación secreta de la Célula Núcleo, y con el coronel Tripp, que busca apoderarse de la fuente de energía.

added.title: La Sed de Poder
added.description: Tras una discusión entre Wynton y Dan, el coronel Tripp controla la mente de Wynton para que ataque la ciudad con Lupitheon. Esto inicia una guerra entre Los Fantásticos y el ejército.

added.title: Un Triunfo Robado
added.description: Dan se embarca en una aventura para superar al nuevo equipo de Peleadores Bakugan de Magnus, pero al final, ellos lo salvarán a él.

added.title: La Aventura de Lightning
added.description: Lightning descubre la Célula Núcleo enterrada bajo tierra, y se enfrenta a Strata El Cazador para intentar proteger su secreto.

added.title: La Venganza de Bao Bao
added.description: Cuando el antiguo compañero de Mao Mao amenaza al reino, los amigos de Mao Mao tendrán que conocer su pasado para proteger el presente.

added.title: Enemigo Mimo
added.description: Cuando el departamento del sheriff se enfrenta a un monstruo que copia todos los movimientos, tendrán que encontrar el modo de pelear sin pelear.

added.title: No Me Impresiona
added.description: Cuando un Corazoncito no se siente impresionado con las hazañas del departamento del sheriff, nuestros tres héroes intentan de todo para conquistarlo.

added.title: El Mensaje
added.description: Lloyd y su compañero lobo encuentran una cueva y encuentran al Mech adentro. Escuchan un mensaje de Zane que les da una pista de su destino.

added.title: El Hacedor de Fuego
added.description: El Emperador de Hielo se entera de la llegada de los ninjas y envía a sus guerreros Samurais Blizzard a destruirlos, y a todos los aldeanos que los albergaron.

added.title: Un Aliado Peculiar
added.description: Lloyd se enfrenta a los Samurais Blizzard del Emperador de Hielo, pero es rescatado por un lobo extraño con quien desarrolla una amistad peculiar.

added.title: El Peor Ninja de Todos
added.description: De regreso en ciudad Ninjago, tres criminales se enteran de la ausencia de los ninjas y organizan una fuga de la prisión Kryptarium, contando historias sobre cómo fueron capturados mientras avanzaban.

added.title: Papel de Bano Bebecin
added.description: Manzana necesita conseguir la provisión del papel higiénico que usaría en toda su vida para terminar su escultura de arte moderno.

added.title: Conquista de Popularidad
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao descubre que no es tan popular como Colosal y Adorabat, sus amigos deciden reinventarlo en forma de un héroe más amable y tierno.

added.title: Superado
added.description: Cuando Rufus y Reg llegan para engañar al pueblo, el sheriff Mao Mao les enseña una lección sobre la justicia.

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: El Trampolin de Hamburguesa
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben encontrar una manera de usar el trampolín de Hamburguesa sin que él se sienta usado.

added.title: Manzana Mandona
added.description: Manzana queda a cargo de la Tienda de Dolar por primera vez.

added.title: No es Gracioso
added.description: Cuando se acerca el aniversario de seis meses de amistad, Manzana tiene que encontrar una manera de no perder a su mejor amigo.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee enlists washed-up TV show host Meteorfire to help him find another of Windblade's psychic shards on Luna-3.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 2
added.description: Bumblebee runs the gauntlet of creepily haunted Luna-3, while Meteorfire records everything on camera for his show.

added.title: Pesadilla de Verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y Amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: Aventura en el Laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: Atrapados en la Jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Demonios Internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Una Extrana Conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

removed.title: To Air Is Robot
removed.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

removed.title: The Explorer's Club
